<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Exasperate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Exasperate,</orth> vb. to provoke, to make angry: <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 1, 60</bibl>. Unchanged in the partic.: <cit><quote>why art thou then e.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this report hath so e. the king,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.6.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 6, 38</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>